    {
      "id": "6owJX1dkqzQw-KUcfifFK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 159.11328125,
      "y": 455.25,
      "width": 748.5877685546875,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 70,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1937534799,
      "version": 474,
      "versionNonce": 1232555553,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781979770121,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Suppose we have an object, that's going through state changes and after\nsome changes, it became unstable.\nHence, we want after each change we can take a snapshot and store\nsomewhere, so that it can later be restored back.\n\nWe can also use it for: \n- Version-Management\n- implement Undo/Redo\n- find and restore to older versions. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Suppose we have an object, that's going through state changes and after some changes, it became unstable.\nHence, we want after each change we can take a snapshot and store somewhere, so that it can later be restored back.\n\nWe can also use it for: \n- Version-Management\n- implement Undo/Redo\n- find and restore to older versions. ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
